Contractors: Your authorized consultants and service providers may use the Software on your behalf, provided they adhere to the confidentiality standards herein.

3. TECHNICAL SAFEGUARDS & SYSTEM STABILITY
The Software is provided in an obfuscated binary form. This measure is implemented for two critical professional reasons:

Operational Safety: Given the high-precision nature of the Ternary‑Over‑Windows (T.O.W.) logic, any unauthorized or accidental modification to the internal binary structure could lead to critical system failure. Obfuscation serves as a protective layer to prevent such displacements and maintain the stability of your deployment.

IP Protection: To protect the trade secrets of the NanoSIREN engine and DAEMONLab’s core intellectual property.

4. PRESERVATION OF CORE TECHNOLOGY
Licensees agree to the following professional standards:

Binary Integrity: Unless expressly authorized in writing, reverse engineering or any attempt to de-obfuscate the Software is restricted to protect its functional stability and proprietary trade secrets.

Technical Respect: Circumventing technical protections or redistributing the Software "as-is" without authorization is prohibited.

5. CONFIDENTIALITY
The parties acknowledge that the scoring methods and isolation logic of XN.CORE constitute sensitive intellectual property. You agree to maintain the confidentiality of non-public technical documentation and not disclose internal architectural details to third parties.

6. FLEXIBILITY & CUSTOM TERMS
This license is a baseline for professional cooperation. DAEMONLab remains open to negotiating specific addendums for white-label distribution, specific technology transfers, or customized service-level agreements (SLA).

